        Alternate Method   To get a fully automated solution your could do the following command:  $ module -l avail 2 1 | grep  ^f  | wc -l  Where:   module -l avail : lists all modules (in long format, i.e. one per line)  2 1 : merges output from  standard error  to the  standard output  so it can be feed into grep.  For some reason the
developers of the  module  command thought it was a good idea to output the module names on the  error  stream rather than
the logical  output  stream.  grep "^f" : only shows lines beginning with  f  wc -l : counts the number of lines      
